<div class='communityQuestionSubTitle'>
Popular Answered Questions
</div>
<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1439911-i-am-curious-i-watched-a-documentary">I am curious; I watched a documentary titled Rwanda&#39;s Untold Story some time ago*, which seemed pretty serious about its claims that the Tutsis carried out a massive slaughter of Hutus as well. Is this book&#39;s view on Paul Kagame realistic, or only the official account that makes him look like a knight on a white horse?
https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/mar/02/bbc-rwanda-documentary-inquiry</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1439911'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F11472.We_Wish_to_Inform_You_That_Tomorrow_We_Will_Be_Killed_with_Our_Families">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1439911-i-am-curious-i-watched-a-documentary">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1439911-i-am-curious-i-watched-a-documentary">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/19519768-pat-kelly"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1366221247i/19519768._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/19519768-pat-kelly">Pat Kelly</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Sometimes you have to read more than two books to have the full picture of a situation. To understand the massacre of the Tutsi, you would have to und<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Sometimes you have to read more than two books to have the full picture of a situation. To understand the massacre of the Tutsi, you would have to understand the decades and systems that led up to it. I am not going to try to change you mind. But I will say this, the genocide in Rwanda was not about Paul Kagame. Hundreds of thousands of people died, thousands of rapes occurred, several children were orphaned. Each life lost cannot be reduced to which side should receive your sympathies.<br />When I was ten, I saw the hundreds of bloated bodies on the lake. As an adult, I had the honour of spending 8 years in Rwanda in my early 30s. When you see the scars, when you hear the stories. When you live in a nation with an evident gap of people of a certain age, It is almost ridiculous to pay mind to who the hero should be. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

